main event: On May 26, 1953, a single unidentified object was observed in Ashland, Kentucky, described as high-pitched and dull grayish-silver, increasing and then diminishing in size during its flight.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 30 seconds., The object was visually observed but had insufficient data for detailed analysis., Report categorized as unreliable due to lack of concrete details., Observers were encouraged to disregard the event as an unfounded story., The Project Blue Book documentation indicates a formal procedure for reporting UFO sightings.
